.TH "elfling" "1" "2026-06-09" "elfling User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
elfling - a linking compressor for ELF files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]elfling\f[R] [\f[B]-o\f[R]\f[I]output\f[R]]
[\f[B]-c\f[R]\f[I]params\f[R]] [\f[B]-l\f[R]\f[I]library\f[R]]\&...
[\f[B]-f\f[R]\f[I]flag\f[R]]\&...
\f[I]file.o\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]elfling\f[R] is a context-modeling compressing linker that
transforms an ELF relocatable object file (\f[I].o\f[R]) into a minimal
self-decompressing ELF executable.
It is inspired by \f[B]Crinkler\f[R], a compressing linker for the
Windows demoscene, and targets the Linux demoscene where executable size
is critical.
.PP
\f[B]elfling\f[R] reads a single ELF object file (i386 or x86_64),
resolves symbol relocations, builds an import jump table using a
hash-based dynamic linker stub, compresses the resulting code and data
with an adaptive arithmetic context model, and writes a
self-decompressing ELF binary embedding the decompression stub.
.PP
The following limitations apply in the current version:
.IP \[bu] 2
Only a single input object file is supported.
.IP \[bu] 2
Only SDL 1.2 and OpenGL library imports are resolved at run time; the
\f[B]-l\f[R] option is parsed but ignored for library resolution.
.IP \[bu] 2
Some ELF section types and relocation types may not be handled and may
cause a crash.
.IP \[bu] 2
Running i386 output on a 64-bit system requires the matching 32-bit
runtime libraries.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]-o\f[R]\f[I]output\f[R]
Write the compressed executable to \f[I]output\f[R].
Default: \f[B]c.out\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]-c\f[R]\f[I]params\f[R]
Set the compression context configuration.
\f[I]params\f[R] is a hexadecimal string encoding the weight and size of
each arithmetic context (up to 16 contexts).
When omitted, default parameters are used automatically.
Example: \f[B]-c0801010205070b0b0734273ac30403158d\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]-l\f[R]\f[I]library\f[R]
Declare a shared library dependency (e.g., \f[B]-llibc.so.6\f[R],
\f[B]-llibSDL-1.2.so.0\f[R], \f[B]-llibGL.so.1\f[R]).
This option is parsed but currently ignored; SDL 1.2 and OpenGL are the
only libraries resolved at run time.
.TP
\f[B]-f\f[R]\f[I]flag\f[R]
Enable a boolean flag.
\f[I]flag\f[R] is appended directly to \f[B]-f\f[R] with no separator.
Recognized flags:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]verbose\f[R]
Print detailed information about sections, imports, and relocations
during linking.
Enabled with \f[B]-fverbose\f[R].
.RE
.SH OUTPUT
.PP
\f[B]elfling\f[R] prints progress to standard output during linking:
.TP
\f[B]Arch: i386\f[R] or \f[B]Arch: x86_64\f[R]
Detected architecture of the input object file.
.TP
\f[B]Section\f[R] \f[I]name\f[R] **\[at]** \f[I]address\f[R]
Virtual address assigned to each section in the output image.
.TP
\f[B]Wrote\f[R] \f[I]N\f[R] \f[B]bytes\f[R]
Size of the final compressed executable in bytes.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Compress a 32-bit C program:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
gcc -Os -c prog.c -fomit-frame-pointer -fno-exceptions -o prog.o -m32
elfling prog.o -oprog.out -llibc.so.6
chmod 755 prog.out
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Compress a 64-bit program with explicit compression parameters:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
gcc -Os -c prog.c -fomit-frame-pointer -fno-exceptions -o prog.o
elfling prog.o -oprog.out -c0801010205070b0b0734273ac30403158d -llibc.so.6
chmod 755 prog.out
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Compress an SDL/OpenGL demo with verbose output:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
gcc -Os -c demo.c -fomit-frame-pointer -fno-exceptions -ffast-math \[rs]
    -fsingle-precision-constant -o demo.o -m32
elfling demo.o -odemo.out -llibSDL-1.2.so.0 -llibGL.so.1 -fverbose
\f[R]
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[B]test/tmp\f[R]
Temporary file created during linking.
Contains the uncompressed linked binary before compression.
Overwritten on each run.
.SH BUGS
.IP \[bu] 2
Only one input object file can be linked at a time.
.IP \[bu] 2
Library flags (\f[B]-l\f[R]) are ignored; SDL 1.2 and OpenGL are always
assumed.
.IP \[bu] 2
Some ELF relocation types or unusual section layouts may cause a crash.
.IP \[bu] 2
32-bit output on a 64-bit system requires 32-bit compatibility
libraries.
.PP
Report bugs at \f[B]https://github.com/google/elfling\f[R].
.SH AUTHORS
.PP
Written by Minas and Calodox.
Packaged for Debian by Nicolas HOUDELOT <nicolas@demosdebs.org>.
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
